# Git Commit Conventions

All commits must follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) specification.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

## Commit Types

- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code refactoring (no behavior change)
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, no logic change)
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks (config, build, dependencies)
- `perf`: Performance improvements

## Scope

Use the area of codebase affected:
- `core`: Core singletons (TimeManager, EventBus, DataManager, GameLoop)
- `models`: Data models (ShipClass, Fleet, Colony, etc.)
- `systems`: Simulation systems (EconomySystem, FleetSystem, etc.)
- `ui`: User interface scripts and scenes
- `gamestate`: GameState singleton
- `scene`: Scene files (.tscn)
- `config`: Configuration files

## Subject

- Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
